&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of the Manual Styleguide is to describe the stylistic conventions to be used to develop user support&#xD;
    materials. A Manual Styleguide gives advice on, and rules for, spelling general and domain-specific terms, sentence&#xD;
    style, and technical writing issues.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
  <representationOptions>&lt;a id=&quot;Tailoring&quot; name=&quot;Tailoring&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A Manual Styleguide is needed if there is a significant amount of user documentation, including both printed and&#xD;
    on-line documentation.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Use existing styleguides, such as [&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/customcategories/references_56F06DFD.html#HAC97&quot; guid=&quot;7.755968586980351E-308&quot;>HAC97&lt;/a>] and [&lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/customcategories/references_56F06DFD.html#MOS98&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;7.755968586980351E-308&quot;>MOS98&lt;/a>], as there are few good books available on this topic.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></representationOptions>
